      "headline": "The Wunderteam Falls Short",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "id": "fastest-goal-conceded",
          "label": "FASTEST GOAL CONCEDED",
          "story": "Ernst Lehner needed only 25 seconds to beat Austria in the third-place match in Naples — a record for the fastest goal in World Cup history that stood until 1962. It capped a bitter finish for Sindelar's Wunderteam, tournament favorites who fell just short of the final."
        }
      ],
